06508nam a22009015i 9789814279277DE-B159720221201113901.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||221201t20092009si     fo  d z      eng d  a2010353016  a97898142792777 a10.1355/97898142792772doi  a(DE-B1597)492369  a(OCoLC)1041994757  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  asicSG00aHF1583b.A629 2009 7aPOL0110202bisacsh0481pa320qDE-10100aAPEC at 20 :bRecall, Reflect, Remake /ced. by Hank Lim, K. Kesavapany. 1aSingapore : bISEAS Publishing, c[2009] 4c©2009  a1 online resource (140 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tForeword -- tPreface -- tAbout the Authors -- tCHAPTER 1 APEC: Genesis and Challenges -- tCHAPTER 2 APEC’s Origins and its Future -- tCHAPTER 3 Four Adjectives Become a Noun: APEC The Future of Asia-Pacific Cooperation -- tCHAPTER 4 APEC’s Eye on the Prize: Participants, Modality, and Confidence-Building -- tAPEC: Taking Stock and Looking Ahead -- tCHAPTER 6 Revamping APEC’s Concerted Unilateral Liberalization -- tCHAPTER 7 APEC at 20: Assessment of Trade/Investment Liberalization, Facilitation and Ecotech Activities -- tCHAPTER 8 Integrating the Business Community in the APEC Process: Genesis of the Pacific Business Forum -- tAPPENDICES Appendix 1 APEC Member Economies: General Economic Indicators -- tAppendix 2 Merchandise Trade in APEC, 1989 -- tAppendix 3 Merchandise Trade in APEC, 2008 -- tAppendix 4 Regional Trade Agreements (RTAs) in Force among APEC Member Economies -- tAppendix 5 Regional Trade Agreements (RTAs) among APEC Member Economies for which an Early Announcement has been made to the WTO -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aSpanning 20 years of history, the achievements of APEC may seem uneventful in the eyes of some observers. Yet careful deliberation will point to APEC's many remarkable high points as well as some of the challenges. The foundations of APEC were set in place about 40 years ago based on the achievements of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) and the Pacific Economic Cooperation Council (PECC). One of the cornerstones of APEC's vision is to achieve a free and open trade area among its member economies. This vision is anchored in the Bogor Goals that remain the centrepiece of the APEC process. The Bogor Goals represent a cause for celebration as well as angst. Celebration because the region has moved towards achieving a much more liberalized environment of trading and investment since 1989, angst because the deadlines for achieving the goals have not yet been fully realized. Today, APEC embraces many of the world's dynamic developed and developing economies that are better poised to meet the new challenges of this century. For those seeking to get a quick sweep of APEC, this book recalls, reflects and provides enough food for thought on the possible remake of APEC. The chapters are carefully written by experts who have been directly involved in the APEC process one way or another. The invaluable insights serve to place the whole APEC process in a balanced perspective, yet with candid deliberations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aAsian cooperation. 0aPacific Area cooperation. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / Trade & Tariffs.2bisacsh1 aChan, Man-jung Mignonne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDrysdale, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElek, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKesavapany, K., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKoh, Tommy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLim, Hank, eed